  "cross_reference_notes": "## Executive Summary: Anto Antony\n\n### Overall Assessment\nAnto Antony (Indian National Congress) represents Pathanamthitta, Kerala. The current composite transparency score is 51.5/100 with low overall data confidence. Anto Antony shows moderate transparency with a score of 51.5/100. No criminal cases declared. High parliament attendance. Active in questions and debates. Data confidence is low — scores should be interpreted with caution.\n\n### Fund Utilization & Development\nConstituency-level MPLADS figures for the 18th Lok Sabha are not published in a consistently accessible machine-readable source at this time. The legacy MoSPI/data.gov.in dataset covers older Lok Sabha terms and the eSAKSHI portal is treated as unavailable unless a per-constituency record is positively matched. This profile therefore marks MPLADS as unavailable rather than estimating fund amounts. Use the RTI template below for constituency-level verification.\n\n### Financial Transparency\nThe available financial record reports asset declaration values are not available from the current open-data cache. Asset fields are based on available open affidavit/declared data and should be interpreted with the stated source confidence of unavailable.\n\n### Legal & Criminal Standing\nNo criminal cases are declared in the available affidavit-derived data. Criminal-record confidence is unavailable.\n\n### Parliamentary Performance\nParliamentary activity currently records attendance at 80.0%, 61 questions, 10 debates and 0 private member bill(s). Committee membership data is not available or shows no committee assignment in the current cache. Legislative record fields show 0 bills introduced, 0 zero-hour mention(s) and 0 special mention(s), with unavailable source confidence.\n\n### Public Engagement & Accessibility\nPublic accessibility data has low confidence: 0 tracked social platform(s), 0 aggregate followers, and 10 recent/news-cache article(s) (0 positive, 1 negative, 9 neutral). Informational compensation data records total monthly compensation/allowances of Rs 2.45 lakh.\n\n### Data Quality & Caveats\nValidation recorded 3 warning(s) and 0 error-level flag(s). Low-confidence dimensions: criminal record, assets, mplads. State/national CAG context includes 7 MPLADS-related audit finding(s), used as context rather than direct proof against the MP. Missing or unavailable open-data fields are displayed explicitly rather than filled with estimates.\n\n### Key Takeaway\nAnto Antony's profile is complete in the sense that every major dashboard section now has either data-backed values or an explicit availability caveat. The most important follow-up for this profile is to verify constituency-level MPLADS releases and expenditure through official RTI/departmental records because the public machine-readable sources are currently incomplete for the 18th Lok Sabha.",
